<TITLE> IFC pledges more SME support </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 13 (bdnews24.com)  The International Finance Corporation has pledged to expand its operations to promote the private sector in Bangladesh, and extend more support to small and medium enterprises in particular. The IFC South Asian regional team, led by its vice president Farida Khambata, met with finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam on Monday in Washington DC, on the sidelines of the annual World Bank-IMF meetings, the Bangladesh Embassy in the US said in a statement. The IFC assured the finance adviser that it would also provide required support to the Better Business Forum and the Regulatory Reforms Commission to improve the investment climate for private sector development. It said that it was now in the process of strengthening its office in Dhaka. bd
